-- Brazilian Stock Movers: Petrobras, PDG Realty Rise as HRT Sinks
-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 2012-01-03T20:26:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-03/brazilian-stock-movers-ccr-pdg-realty-advance-hrt-declines.html
The following companies had  unusual (IBOV) 
price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading. Preferred
shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The  Bovespa (IBOV)  index advanced 2.5 percent to 59,264.87.  HRT Participacoes em Petroleo SA (HRTP3)  (HRTP3 BS) plunged 13
percent to 505 reais, a record low. The company said its 1-HRT-
4-AM onshore well in  Brazil ’s northern Solimoes Basin may
produce as much as 250,000 cubic meters of natural gas and 300
barrels of condensate a day after concluding formation tests,
according to a regulatory filing. The company was expected to
also find oil in the well, according to Ricardo Correa, an
analyst at Rio de Janeiro-based brokerage Ativa SA.  PDG Realty SA Empreendimentos & Participacoes (PDGR3)  (PDGR3 BS)
climbed 1.9 percent to 6.35 reais. Brazil’s biggest homebuilder
by revenue said in a filing its fourth-quarter contracted sales
rose 16 percent from a year earlier to 2.04 billion reais ($1.11
billion).  Petroleo Brasileiro SA (PETR4)  (PETR4 BS) added 3.9 percent to
22.41 reais. Brazil’s state-controlled oil company said it found
crude and natural gas of “excellent quality” at the Tambuata
well in the Golfinho field off the country’s southeastern coast,
according to a regulatory filing today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
